INTERIOR POINTS may be given to adjust the length of 
tetrahedra edges around theses points as vertices.
The WISHED LENGTH of tetrahedra edges around the POINT
is an upper BOUND.

Example:
PTI1; PTI2; {the interior points}
0.01; 0.5;  {the lengths around each interior points}

The tetrahedra edges from PT1 will have a length<0.01
The tetrahedra edges from PT2 will have a length<0.5
